value.0: Predatory blue eyes keep careful watch on the surroundings, including you. One could not easily mistake this wolf for a dog. However, unlike its brethren which stalk the wilds this one seems to have been somewhat domesticated. While the guards of Forrstakkr have found a way to domesticate the wild wolves, it seems unlikely they would take as kindly to outsiders.

Hardened by the hostile environment, trained extensively and outfitted with high quality equipment, the men and women of the Forrstakkr Guard are a more than capable fighting force in the harsh northern environment. Augmented by veterans from the Ostland conflict, this force is quite ready to protect and fight for the people of Forrstakkr.

With gear suited to the cold and frozen surroundings, these well trained and keen eyed rangers look as though they would be able to almost disappear into the wild when needed. Acting as the eyes and ears of Forrstakkr, as well as the first line of defense, they are all dedicated to protecting the people of Forrstakkr from whatever may threaten.
This magic bow has a bonus to attack. As well, it allows the wielder to add part of his strength modifier to the damage dealt.

Welcome to the Nation of Forrstakkr

Our laws are the following:

- Barak Runedarians, Palemasters, and Tiamatians are banished from Forrstakkr.

- Civilians attempting to leave into the wilds should not do so without proper equipment and supplies.

- Outsiders harassing the locals will not be tolerated.

- Weapons, bows and magical staffs are not to be flaunted or waved dangerously and are to be kept away when not needed.

- No unauthorized magic within public areas of the settlements.

- Pets larger than a wolf are not allowed without special permit.

- No thievery, murdering, causing scenes or committing fraud.

- No sneaking in the settlement.

- No undead, demons or devils within the settlements. Tieflings are allowed as long as they behave.

Most importantly, respect our nation, its denizens and the Guard. And you will be respected in turn.

During times of emergency, follow the orders and instructions of the Guard.
Laws of the Nation of Forrstakkr

((This is a Job System resource. Click to interact.))
Change the name of this waypoint into the name of the template you want to use.

This description flows out of the window. Make sure you read all of it.

Names
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The waypoint's name, tag and resref must be the same. It MUST start with "tst_" and I advice to use a descriptive phrase for the rest of the name. Look at the available waypoints for examples. You can use up to 12 characters.

Variables
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
tst_boss_switch: set to 1 to spawn the boss blueprint
tst_max_1: maximum amount of spawntype 1
tst_resref_1: buleprint of spawntype 1
tst_resref_boss: blueprint id of the boss
tst_spawntypes: the number of spawntypes to use, excluding the boss

Values
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
tst_boss_switch: 0 or 1
tst_max_1: 0 to 5
tst_resref_1: the resref you find in the properties of a monster
tst_resref_boss: idem
tst_spawntypes: 0 to 4

Mind that you can use one boss and a maximum of 4 spawntypes. Of each spawntype you can spawn up to 5 creatures.
See the description of the  "tst template and decription" blueprint in the toolset.
